  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6599.92 sitting just below the max positive gamma wall at 6605, dealers are positioned to sell any push higher while providing support above the 6590 negative gamma level. The PIN regime with 25.4B in total GEX creates a tight trading range between 6590-6610, where dealers will actively dampen volatility by selling rallies into the 6605/6610 walls and buying dips toward 6590. The GEX surge event suggests increased options flow that's reinforcing these levels, making breakouts difficult until we see a decisive move through either 6590 (downside acceleration) or the 6621 flip point (regime change to negative gamma).\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to stay pinned between 6590-6610 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
